gsonpath

Interface GsonArrayStreamer<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractGsonArrayStreamer

    public interface GsonArrayStreamer<T>
    Exposes functionality to obtain an array directly from a json file without declaring a container class, or extending a collection directly.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  GsonArrayStreamer.StreamCallback<T>
      A callback used when streaming json array content as opposed to reading the entire array into memory.

      • streamArray

        void streamArray(com.google.gson.Gson gson,
               java.io.Reader in,
               GsonArrayStreamer.StreamCallback<T> callback)
                 throws com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException
        Streams a list of objects from a Json array which exists within the reader. Each object is returned one at a time using the callback.

        The streaming can be cancelled at anytime using the GsonArrayStreamer.StreamCallback.StreamHandler object within the callback.

        Parameters:
        gson - standard Gson main class. Must have all the required type adapters defined.
        in - the reader used to create the JsonReader which will read the Json array.
        callback - a callback which returns each individual object within the Json array. The callback exposes a mechanism to stop streaming the Json array using the GsonArrayStreamer.StreamCallback.StreamHandler class.
        Throws:
        com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException - thrown by Gson. Ensure you close your input stream as this method will not close it.

      • streamArraySegmented

        void streamArraySegmented(com.google.gson.Gson gson,
                        java.io.Reader in,
                        int segmentSize,
                        GsonArrayStreamer.StreamCallback<T[]> callback)
                          throws com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException
        Streams a list of objects from a Json array which exists within the reader. An array of objects, of size 'segmentSize' is returned each time the array has been filled.

        The streaming can be cancelled at anytime using the GsonArrayStreamer.StreamCallback.StreamHandler object within the callback.

        Parameters:
        gson - standard Gson main class. Must have all the required type adapters defined.
        in - the reader used to create the JsonReader which will read the Json array.
        callback - a callback which returns each individual object within the Json array. The callback exposes a mechanism to stop streaming the Json array using the GsonArrayStreamer.StreamCallback.StreamHandler class.
        Throws:
        com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException - thrown by Gson. Ensure you close your input stream as this method will not close it.
